<h2>%%ReferenceStyle%%Journal article, multiple articles by same author</h2>
<hr>
<br>
<strong>REFERENCE LIST ENTRY</strong>
<br>
<br>
Add a reference list at the end of your essay citing all sources used in the body of your writing.
<br>
<br>
Different works by the same author(s) are listed in chronological (date) order. If several works 
have the same date as well as the same author, works are distinguished by suffixes a, b, c, etc. 
These are allocated in the reference list where they are ordered alphabetically by title. 
References with the same first author and a different second or third author are listed alphabetically.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	Authors. (Year of publication [suffix]). Title of article. 
	<em>Name of Publication, volume</em>(issue), page numbers. doi:Digital Object Identifier 
	(if assigned)
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Examples</strong>
<br>
<blockquote>
	<div class="ref-hang-indent">
		<span class="hover" title="Authors">Smith, A.</span> 
		(<span class="hover" title="Year of publication">2050</span>). 
		<span class="hover" title="Title of article">Teaming with wildlife: Promoting team development through volunteer service at Auckland Zoo</span>. 
		<em><span class="hover" title="Name of Publication">New Zealand Business Review</span>, 
		<span class="hover" title="volume">17</span></em>(<span class="hover" title="issue">4</span>), 
		<span class="hover" title="page numbers">230&#45;240</span>. 
		doi:<span class="hover" title="Digital Object Identifier">12:3456789012</span>
	</div>
	<div class="ref-hang-indent">
		<span class="hover" title="Authors">Smith, A.</span> 
		(<span class="hover" title="Year of publication">2056</span>). 
